# Demo Generated JS Sync

`packages/extension/demos/generated/**/*.js` is emitted by `tsc` (`build:generated`), not Prettier. **Do not commit** `.js` or `.js.map` — they are gitignored; commit **`generated/**/*.ts`** and **`generated/{product}/scripts/*.mjs`**.

`generated/{product}/mcp-build-generated-at.ts` is the shared MCP build stamp (gitignored). Tool modules re-export it; only this file changes on every `generate:all`.

After clone or `generate:all`, run **`npm run build:generated`** (or save `.db2ai` with the extension) so MCP can load `*.js` locally.

**Do not** add pre-commit logic that rebuilds and `git add`s files during commit. Regenerate explicitly; the user stages the result.

## When to run `npm run generate:all`

From the **db2ai workspace root** (monorepo path — local CLI):

```bash
npm run generate:all
```

Uses `scripts/monorepo-generate-all.mjs` → `packages/cli/bin/cli.js`. **Do not** use demos `generate:all` for monorepo work (that is the VSIX extension-scan path).

Run when any of:

- `packages/cli/src/generator/**` changed
- Demo DSL changed (`packages/extension/demos/*.db2ai`)
- After `@toolfactory.dev/core` pin refresh affecting codegen or MCP host — see [core2ai-consumer-impact.mdc](./core2ai-consumer-impact.mdc)
- `core2ai/src/codegen/**` changed (MCP host templates; run `npm run test` in core2ai after pin refresh)
- `core2ai/src/scripts/**` changed (rewrites `packages/extension/demos/generated/{product}/scripts/**/*.mjs` via `writeGeneratedScripts`)

Always run `build:generated` afterward (below).

`generated/{product}/scripts/*.mjs` holds VSIX utility modules. Hand start/kill catalogs stay under `scripts/`.

## When to run `build:generated` only

From workspace root:

`npm run build:generated --prefix packages/extension/demos`

After:

- Every `generate:all`
- Edits to `packages/extension/demos/generated/**/*.ts` or hooks stubs
- Fresh clone before MCP

## Commit

Include regenerated **`generated/**/*.ts`** (and `generated/{product}/scripts/**/*.mjs` when utility templates change). Do not hand-edit `.js`.

## Verify

Run `npm run check` after regeneration. For generator changes, follow [codegen-generated-quality.mdc](./codegen-generated-quality.mdc).
